✦ IN PROGRESS ✦

Ongoing Research

Currently working on cutting-edge problems at the intersection of propulsion and computational modelling.

Active Research
LPSC · Liquid Propulsion Systems Centre

Modelling of Fuel Regression and Pressure Behaviour in Hybrid Motor

Investigating the coupled dynamics of solid fuel combustion in hybrid rocket motors. Burn rate depends on convective heat transfer to the fuel grain, fuel pyrolysis, and oxidiser flow rate and its evaporation. The project focuses on modelling the pressure-time behaviour and oscillations by coupling LOX evaporation with heat-transfer-based fuel regression.

Developing a conjugate heat-transfer model to predict the pyrolysis rate of HTPB fuel based on heat flux at the fuel surface, with a moving mesh to account for fuel grain recession due to burning — implemented alongside a combustion model in a CFD package to enable full transient pressure behaviour simulation.

What I've Been Up To

🚀
Solid Propellant Rocket Workshop
Built and launched a real solid propellant rocket from scratch — hands-on experience in propellant chemistry, nozzle design, and flight mechanics. One of the most intense and rewarding experiences of my engineering journey.
✈️
DIY UAV Fabrication Workshop
Participated in LPU's Build and Fly event in collaboration with SHYEN — designed, assembled, and flew a hand-made RC glider with my team. From foam sheets to actual flight.
🔬
LG Electronics Internship
Spent a summer at LG Electronics Noida conducting PCB testing and reliability analysis in a real NABL-accredited lab — operating industry-grade machinery that most students only read about.
🛸
The Troublemakers
Part of a passionate group of aerospace students who love breaking things to understand them better — collaborating on projects, pushing ideas, and having way too much fun in the process.
